      "description": "Offering a mechanically sound E46 M3 featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six and a tactile 6-speed manual transmission. This example is a driver-focused machine where technical maintenance has been prioritized over concours aesthetics. The VANOS unit has been overhauled for optimal variable valve timing, and the rear subframe has been proactively reinforced to ensure structural rigidity under lateral load. The chassis benefits from a refreshed suspension setup including poly-bushings and tuned dampers, maintaining the precise turn-in and feedback these M-cars are known for. Power delivery remains linear up to the 8,000 RPM redline, managed by a healthy M-Variable limited-slip differential. Recent service includes a valve clearance adjustment and a cooling system refresh, making this a turn-key enthusiast vehicle for the canyon or the track.",
